parameters: Umi "Such an amazing sound... it's calming..."
Kru "Ah, that's the sound of the waves."
Kru "Yes, waves. It's the motion of the sea as it comes in and goes out."
Kru "Ah, let's actually take a look."
Kru "Umi-san... did you think the sea was red?"
Kru "Now that you mention it... indeed..."
Umi "Wow! It's coming this way! Is it alive"
Kru "It's not alive. I don't know why, but the sea moves."

Kru "Haha, Umi is always so scared. How about I hold your hand? Then you
won't be scared, right?"
Kru "I won't let go. Let's go in!"
Umi "Yes! And... it's amazing... it really feels like it's alive..."

Kru "Yeah. It's true. There are many creatures living in the sea... and
they live being rocked by these waves..."

Kru "Yeah. The sea is very vast and deep... when you come here, you're just
overwhelmed by its enormity..."
Kru "Yeah. Probably much vaster than you can imagine."

Umi "I see. So if we ride the waves, we could escape from unpleasant
things, right?"

Umi "Whoa! My feet got swept away! Whoa whoa whoa! It's salty! It tastes
like salt!"
Kru "Hahaha! Yes, yes! The sea is all made up of saltwater!"
Umi "Mmm. Kru is laughing at me... you!"
Kru "Whoa! Whoa! It's cold! Umi-san! Stop it!"
Umi "Kyah! Kru is teasing me! Hahaha!"
Umi "Thank you for bringing me here!"
Kru "Eh? I can't hear you over the sound of the waves!"
Umi "I love you Kru I really love you"
Kru "Eh I can't hear anything at all! What"

We played, forgetting how time flew by... Umi's innocent laughter shone
brightly, bathed in the sunlight reflecting off the water's surface...

Could there be anything more beautiful in this world...? I can't express it
well, being uneducated, but I thought this moment was the most beautiful in
my life.

I wanted to remember everything about this moment... the blurry island in
the distance, the shadows of the trees, the heat of the sandy beach, and
vowed to never forget them.

I had never wished for anything before, but now I finally understood how it
felt to wish for something.

Hey, Umi... what were you saying earlier...? Were you saying something
usual like 'I'm hungry' or 'Kru is an idiot'...?

But seeing that carefree smile, I knew Umi was truly happy. I wanted to
continue that joy into tomorrow, the day after, and forever.
If it could be my role... if it could be the meaning of my life...

Would it be presumptuous to think so...? If allowed, I would become your
shield and your sword to protect that smile...
In your deep, clear red eyes...
